				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Thinking of moving to EVERCRAFT?<a name="73518"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 21 05 10:35 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Thats right EverQUEST II is now EverCRAFT!
<br />

<br />
The name change isn't official yet but thats pretty much the reality of it. So if you are into crafting and want a game thats all about crafting?...it's  EQ II...er EverCRAFT. Pretty much all rules have been changed so adventurers exist to provide items, and a market for the crafters. (virtually all crafted quested gear is now attuneable)
<br />

<br />
The only hitch is where the players will get the money to buy the crafted stuff. Maybe foraging to supply the crafters?
<br />

<br />
There, I feel better now....
<br />

<br />
One of the funniest things I have heard in EQII was a couple of weeks in some guy ranting in ooc about a quest..
<br />

<br />
&quot;I didn't make an ogre monk so I could put on my overalls and sh$tkickers and go out and farm!&quot;
<br />

<br />
I'd really like to find this guy and see what he has to say now, lol.
<br />

<br />
An interesting thread on the changes appears at:
<br />

<br />
http://www.thescoutssanctuary.com/viewtopic.php?p=32416#32416
<br />

<br />
I personally agree more with Ookami on pg 3, but the crafters make their point as well. (I pilfered the EverCraft thing from Ookami..)
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Currently in EQII
