				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Thinking of moving to EVERCRAFT?<a name="73566"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 22 05 2:59 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The name change isn't official yet but thats pretty much the reality of it. So if you are into crafting and want a game thats all about crafting?...it's EQ II...er EverCRAFT. Pretty much all rules have been changed so adventurers exist to provide items, and a market for the crafters. (virtually all crafted quested gear is now attuneable) 
<br />

<br />
The only hitch is where the players will get the money to buy the crafted stuff. Maybe foraging to supply the crafters?</span></blockquote>
<br />
This game can TOTALLY be played without having ANYTHING to do with crafting at all.  Quested and named mob-drops are superior to most crafted stuff.  The coin gain from regular-old grouping is better than most crafters make.  (ESPECIALLY now that certain crafting classes that WERE able to mint coin have been nerfed).
<br />

<br />
Making everything attuned now will indeed create a better market for the crafters.  On the more mature servers, like Permafrost that I recently left, I was forced to offer my crafted Carbonite armors at barely more than cost.  The market was SO flooded with junk from people trying to level up, and SO undermined by the lvl 20 armor quests, that it was just plain stupid.
<br />

<br />
The danger that the game was headed toward was that crafting would end up being nothing but a money-sink hobby for rich, high level players, and most folks could play the entire game and never bother with crafted stuff (exactly what it is in eq1).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
